===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} [[knitten]], from {{etyl|ang}} [[cnyttan]], akin to cnotta 'knot', from the Proto-Germanic root [[knuttjan]], from stem [[knutt]]-. Cognate with Old Norse {{term|knýta}} (Danish {{term|knytte}}) and Northern German {{term|knütten}}.

